yclopedia |date=2012 |publisher=ABC-CLIO |location=Santa Barbara, CA |isbn=978-1-59884-458-0}}\n* {{cite book |last=Waters |first=S. D. |title=Leander |year=1950 |publisher=Historical Publications Branch, Department of Internal Affairs, Government of New Zealand |location=Wellington, NZ |series=The Official History of New Zealand in the Second World War 1939\u20131945 |accessdate=28 February 2016 |chapter=Protection of Red Sea Convoys |pages=1\u20137 |chapter-url=http://nzetc.victoria.ac.nz/tm/scholarly/tei-WH2-2Epi-c3-WH2-2Epi-d.html |edition=online |via=New Zealand Electronic Text Centre |oclc=1003719}}\n\n{{World War II}}\n\n[[Category:Convoys of World War II]]\n[[Category:History of the Red Sea]]\n[[Category:Conflicts in 1940]]\n[[Category:East African Campaign (World War II)]]\n[[Category:Regia Marina]]\n[[Category:Naval battles of World War II involving Italy]]\n[[Category:Naval battles of World War II involving the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Naval battles of World War II involving Australia]]\n[[Category:Naval battles of World War II involving New Zealand]]\n[[Category:October 1940 events]]\n", "name_user": "Keith-264", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBattle of Harmil Island", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Attack_on_Convoy_BN_7"}
